content: AS THE SCHEDDULE FOR THE ARRIVAL OF THE NEW PRONCIPLE OFFICER HAS DEVELOPED, WE NOW EECT HIM TO SPEND THE WEEK PRIOR TO THE CAT TEAM VISIT ON CONSULTATIONS IN WARSAW.

THIS MEANS HE WOULD ARRIVE IN KRAKOW ONLY ONE OR TWO WORK DAYS PRIOR TO THE CAT TEAMS ARRIVAL AND WOULD HAVE ALMOST NO CHANCE TO OBSERVE THE POSTS OPERATIONS AND MAKE HIS OWN JUDGEMENTS CONCERNING APPROPRIATE CHANGES.
ALSO, THE SENIOR FSNE IN THE VISA SECTION WILL BE ON A PREVIOUS LY SCHEDULED VACATION UNTIL SEPTEMBER 3.
WE BELIEVE IT WOULD NOT BE POSSIBLE TO OBTAIN AN ACCURATE IMPRESSION OF POST OPERATIONS WHI LE THIS PERSON IN ABSENT.
FOR THESE REASONS WE WOULD LIKE TO SUGGEST THAT THE CAT SCHEDULE BE CHANGED SO THAT KRAKOW WOULD BE THE THIRD POST VISITED RATHER THAN THE SECOND.
THIS WOULD PRESUMABLY PUT THE TEAM IN KRAKOW SEPTEM BER 4,5, AND 6.THE TIME FRAME IN WHICH THE TEAM WOULD BE IN POLAND WOULD REMAIN UNCHANGED.
PLEASE ADVISE.
PAZDRAL ']
SUMMARY:
CRIS IS RECEIVING DOLLARS 595,260 FROM AID GRANT, AND REQUESTS ADDITIONAL DOLLARS 1,814,332 TO PROVIDE ADDITIONAL RELIEF AND REHABILITATION THROUGH FEBRUARY 28.

PROGRAM CONSISTS OF FOOD, EMERGENCY SHELTERS, CLOTHING, BLANKETS AND UTENSILS TO BE FUNDED FROM USG GRANT, WITH HEALTH CARE, ADMINISTRATIVE COSTS, AND PERMANENT RECONSTRUCTION MEASURES COVERED BY RESOURCES DONATED BY OTHERS IN A LONGER TIME FRAME.
MISSION SUPPORTS THIS REQUEST.
END SUMMARY.
AFTER A SERIES OF MEETINGS CRS STAFF DONALD CROSSON AND FATHER MCVEIGH OF CRS/NEW YORK PRESENTED DECEMBER 16 FORMAL REQUEST FOR ADDITIONAL OFDA FUNDING OF DOLLARS 1,814,332.
ADDED TO ORIGINAL GRANT OF DOLLARS 595,260 FOR THIS DISASTER, THE TOTAL REQUIRED BY CRS WOULD BE DOLLARS 2,409,592. 3.
AS YOU KNOW EACH VOLAG OPERATES DIFFERENTLY.
CRS WORKS (IN THIS DISASTER) THROUGH 14 PARISHES OR DIOCESES, NINE IN TAMIL NADU AND 5 IN ANDHRA PRADESH.
EACH DIOCESE DEVELOPS ITS OWN RELIEF PROGRAM AND FUNDS ARE MADE AVAILABLE FROM MULTIPLE SOURCES TO CARRY THE PROGRAMS OUT INCLUDING FUNDS FROM AID/OFDA THROUGH CRS/INDIA.
THUS CRS DOES NOT DIRECTLY CONTROL RELIEF ACTIVITIES AND DOES NOT HAVE A CENTRALLY CONTROLLED UNIFORM PLAN OF RELIEF. 4.
AFTER CAREFUL EVALUATION OF THE VARYING STRENGTHS AND WEAKNESSES OF THE DIFFERENT DIOCESES, CRS HAS DEVELOPED A PROPOSAL DIOCESE BY BIOCESE FOR ACTIVITIES THROUGH FEBRUARY 28, 1978.
THE AMOUNT REQUESTED WILL FUND A PROGRAM WHICH
CRS, LIKE OTHER US VOLAGS HERE BELIEVES FALLS SHORT OF TOTAL NEEDS BUT REPRESENTS THE MOST THEY BELIEVE THEIR ORGANIZATIONS CAN DO IN A WELL RUN,CAREFULLY MANAGED PROGRAM.
TO INSURE THAT OBJECTIVES ARE BEING MET AND FUNDS PROPERLY SPENT CRS WILL FREQUENTLY REVIEW THE ORGANIZATIONS BOOKS AND RELEASE FUNDS TO EACH AS REQUIRED AND JUSTIFIED BY PROGRESS ACHIEVED. 5.

FOLLOWING RUPEE AMOUNTS REQUESTED ARE AT A RATE OF RUPEES 8.50 EQUALS ONE US DOLLAR: (A) TAMIL NADU: FOOD 177,640; CLOTHING/BLANKETS, 1,026,250; UTENSILS, 674,000; SHELTER, 6,022,110 (AT AVERAGE OF RUPEES 850 PER UNIT).
(B) ANDHRA PRADESH: FOOD 4,539,600; CLOTHING/BLANKETS, 1,294,316; UTENSILS NONE; SHELTER, 6,747,622.
TOTAL IS RUPEES 20,481,538 OR DOLLARS 2,409,592.
OF WHICH DOLLARS 595,260 IS ALREADY GRANTED.
TO OBTAIN QUANTITIES OF VICTIMS ASSISTED, CALCULATE RUPEES 25 PER FAMILY FOR UTENSILS (CONSISTING OF COOK POT, LARGE COOK POT, LADLES, FOOD STORAGE TINS, PLATES AND MUGS)
CLOTTING OR BLANKETS AT RUPEES 20 PER BENEFICIARY, FOOD CONSISTS MOSTLY OF RICE, WITH SOME CHILIES, PULSES, AND CONDIMENTS.
OIL IF NEEDED, WILL BE OBTAINED FROM CRS STOCKS.
CRS AUTHORIZES RUPEES 1.50 PER DAY FOR ADULTS AND RUPEES .85 DAILY FOR A CHILD FOR FOOD.
WE QUESTIONED CRS CLOSELY ON NEED TO USE OFDA FUNDS TO BUY RICE.

AFTER EXPLORING OPTIONS OF BORROWING PL 480 RICE FROM REGULAR PROGRAMS (SHORT SUPPLY AND FAR AWAY), DIVERSION OF SHIP WITH PL 480 RICE (NO TIME) AND BORROWING FROM GOVERNMENT ON REPLACEMENT OR NON REPLACEMENT BASIS (THIS WOULD TAKE A LONG TIME), WE RELUCTANTLY CONCLUDED THAT TO MAINTAIN THE RELIEF EFFORT IT IS INDEED NECESSARY TO LOCALLY PURCHASE THE RICE.
CRS LIKE CARE AND CWS BELIEVES THAT 90 DAY LIMIT IS UNREALISTIC AND THAT MORE IS NEEDED AND COULD BE DONE IF LONGER PERIOD WERE PERMITTED.
BUT WE BELIEVE THAT ALTHOUGH THIS MAY BE TRUE OF SHELTER AND VOCATIONAL REHABILITATION, OTHER ELEMENTS OF RELIEF ON A MASS SCALE SHOULD BE COMPLETED BY FEBRUARY 28. 8.

CRS HAS EXPENDED FOLLOWING AMOUNTS (IN DOLLARS)CHARGEABLE TO AID/OFDA GRANT MONEY: FOOD 54,164; CLOTHING 156,428; UTENSILS, 46,773; SHELTER 48,541; AND BLANKETS, 2,117; A TOTAL OF DOLLARS 308,023 SPENT BY SIX CENTERS REPORTING.
AS OTHER CENTERS REPORT IN ACCORDANCE WITH REQUEST BY OFDA REP FOR EXPENDITURE DATA, THIS TOTAL WILL OBVIOUSLY RISE.
IN ADDITION TO CRS FUNDS THE FOLLOWING ORGANIZATIONS HAVE CONTRIBUTED TOWARDS CYCLONE RELIEF (THROUGH THE DIOCESES)

THE FOLLOWING AMOUNTS (IN DOLLARS): ANDHRA PRADESH TAMILNADU CARITAS INDIA 156,470 71,294 PAPAL FUNDS 57,647 42,353 MISEREOR/IGSSS 84,000 28,823 THESE FUNDS WILL BE USED FOR NEEDS NOT MET BY OFDA GRANT FUNDS SUCH AS HEALTH CARE, ADMINISTRATIVE COSTS, RECONSTRUCTION OF HOUSES, AGRICULTURAL INPUTS, ETC. 9.
CRS IS PREPARING DATA ON REQUIREMENTS FOR RECONSTRUCTION AND WILL SUBMIT PROPOSALS TO THEIR HEADQUARTERS FOR OBTAINING FUNDS.
WE HAVE REVIEWED THE CRS PROPOSAL CAREFULLY AND ASKED THEM, IF THE FUNDS REQUESTED OF OFDA CANNOT BE FULLY MET, WHAT AREA HAS LOWEST PRIORITY.
ALTHOUGH THEY FIRMLY WANT THE FULL AMOUNT REQUESTED, WHEN PUSHED THEY IDENTIFIED FOOD AS THE LOWEST PRIORITY AMONG HIGH PRIORITY REQUIREMENTS.
WE SUPPORT THIS CRS REQUEST FOR AN ADDITIONAL GRANT OF DOLLARS 1,814,332 TO CARRY OUT CYCLONE RELIEF. 12.
PLEASE ADVISE.
BLOOD ']

WHEN I MET WITH KREISKY JULY 5 HE INFORMED ME THAT HE AND WILLY BRANDT WILL MEET WITH PLO LEADER ARAFAT IN VIENNA ON JULY 7 AND 8.

KREISKY SAID THAT THEY WILL ASK ARAFAT PLAINLY TO DEFINE THE ATTITUDE OF THE PLO TOWARD ISRAEL: IN OTHER WORDS, DOES THE PLO STILL INSIST THAT ISRAEL MUST BE DESTROYED OR IS IT NOW READY TO RECOGNIZE THE EXISTENCE OF THIS NATION?
KREISKY SAID THEY WILL URGE ARAFAT PUBLICLY TO ENTER INTO CONTACT AND NEGOTIATIONS WITH ISRAEL, THEREBY RECOGNIZING THE EXISTENCE OF THIS STATE. 3.
KREISKY WENT ON TO SAY THAT "WE SOCIALISTS (THE SOCIALIST INTERNATIONAL) CAN NO LONGER ALLOW THE COMMUNISTS TO HAVE A MONOPOLY ON RELATIONS WITH THE PLO" AND THEREFORE THIS MOVE IS BEING MADE.
HE SAID THAT THERE WILL BE GREAT TROUBLE WITH THE OPPOSITION PRESS IN AUSTRIA AND THAT ISRAEL WILL OF COURSE BE UPSET BY THIS NEW MOVE AS WAS THE CASE WHEN HE FIRST MET WITH SADAT.
HOWEVER, THEY FEEL THAT THIS STEP MUST BE TAKEN. 4.
KREISKY STATED THAT HE HAD TRIED TO PREPARE A PAPER RECENTLY WHICH WOULD PERMIT THE PLO GRACIOUSLY TO MOVE TOWARD RELATIONS WITH ISRAEL BUT THAT IT IS NOT YET COM- PLETED.
HE STATED THAT HE EXPECTED ARAFAT WILL TRY TO REPEAT POSITIONS TAKEN AT VARIOUS TIMES IN THE PAST DES-
CRIBING PLO WILLINGNESS TO TREAT WITH ISRAEL, AND THEREBY ENABLING HIM TO CIRCUMSCRIBE THE QUESTION OF HIS WILLING- NESS TO DEAL DIRECTLY WITH ISRAEL.
KREISKY CONTINUED THAT THERE WILL BE A TERRIBLE NOISE ABOUT THIS IN ISRAEL, BUT "WE MUST DO IT."
FURTHERMORE, HE ASSERTED THAT SADAT IS VERY HAPPY ABOUT THIS MEETING AND SUPPORTS IT, HOPING THEREBY TO MOVE THE PALESTINIAN QUESTION TOWARD AN AGREE- ABLE SOLUTION.
IN THE COURSE OF OUR DISCUSSION, KREISKY OPINED THAT A SOLUTION FOR THE QUESTION OF JERUSALEM CAN BE FOUND.
HE SAID HE IS NOT A TECHNICIAN ON THIS QUESTION
BUT, AS ROME IS THE CAPITAL OF THE CATHOLIC CHURCH, CERTAINLY SOME SOLUTION CAN BE FOUND TO ASSURE THE INDEPENDENCE AND SAFE- GUARDING OF MOSLEM HOLY PLACES IN JERUSALEM.
HE SAID HE WAS SURE
MAYOR TEDDY KOLLEK OF JERUSALEM CAN FIND A SOLU- TION TO THIS PROBLEM.
FURTHERMORE, HE STATED THAT THE PALESTINIANS, BEING BASICALLY SECULAR RATHER THAN RELI- GIOUS LIKE THE PRESENT IRANIAN STATE, ARE NOT TOO INTER-
ESTED IN THE QUESTION OF JERUSALEM.
WHAT THEY WANT IS THEIR HOMELAND.
KREISKY REITERATED, AS HE HAS IN THE PAST, THAT THE SAUDIS EXAGGERATE ALL THEIR FEELINGS BUT THAT EVENTUALLY WILL ACCEPT DEVELOPMENTS IN THE MIDDLE EAST AND JERUSALEM.
THE ROYAL FAMILY IS PRESENTLY SPLIT ON THE POLICY TOWARD PALESTINE, BUT HE BELIEVES THEY WILL SETTLE DOWN SOON AND COMPOSE THEIR DIFFERENCES.
THE CHANCELLOR TOLD ME THAT HE WOULD KEEP ME INFORMED OF HIS CONVERSATIONS AND MEETINGS WITH ARAFAT.
WOLF ']

WHILE WE KNOW THAT SCHMIDT WAS DEFINITELY FEELING "NOT UP TO PAR" LAST WEEK AND THAT HE IS NOTORIOUSLY IM- PATIENT WITH DETAILS, HIS REPORTED DISMISSAL OF THE IMPORTANCE OF THE MTN NEGOTIATIONS DOESN'T JIBE WITH WHAT WE KNOW OF HIS BASIC POSITION.
MOREOVER, TO LINK THIS TO SCHMIDT'S PRESUMED "GENERAL ATTITUDE TOWARDS THE UNITED STATES" SEEMS TO BE GOING A BIT FAR.

I SPENT A COUPLE OF HOURS WITH DAYAN AT HIS HOME SUNDAY EVENING, JULY 24, TO REVIEW FOR HIM MY IMPRESSIONS OF PRIME MINISTER BEGIN'S VISIT TO WASHINGTON.IN
THE COURSE OF OUR CONVERSATION, HE MADE SEVERAL OBSERVA- TIONS ABOUT RELATED MATTERS WHICH ARE WORTH REPORTING.
DAYAN ACKNOWLEDGED THAT THE VISIT LOOKED FROM HERE AS IF IT HAD GONE
EXTREMELY WELL ON ALL FRONTS.

FRANKLY, HE SAID, BEGIN'S SUCCESS IN REUNITING THE POLITICAL SUPPORT OF AMERICAN JEWRY SOLIDLY BEHIND HIM WAS ONE OF HIS OUTSTANDING ACHIEVEMENTS, TOGETHER WITH THE CLOSE RAPPORT WHICH HE APPARENTLY ESTABLISHED WITH PRESIDENT CARTER.
BUT, DAYAN CONTINUED, DESPITE THE PRESENT EUPHORIC ATMOSPHERE
HE WAS VERY CONCERNED THAT THERE APPARENTLY HAD BEEN NO PROGRESS ON THE KEY ISSUES OF SUBSTANCE WHICH DIVIDED US, ESPECIALLY THE PALESTINIAN PROBLEM.IN

THIS CONNECTION HE WONDERED WHETHER SECRETARY VANCE INTENDED TO GET INTO SERIOUS DISCUSSIONS OF SUBSTANTIVE ALTERNATIVES DURING HIS FORTHCOMING TRIP, OR LIMIT HIMSELF TO OVERCOMING PROCEDURAL OBSTACLES.
(THE CLEAR IMPLICATION IS THAT DAYAN HOPES VERY MUCH
IT WILL BE THE FORMER.)

HE ALSO WAS SKEPTICAL ABOUT THE EXTENT TO WHICH ONE COULD HAVE SERIOUS DISCUSSIONS IN NEW YORK WITH THE ARAB FOREIGN MINISTERS DURING THE UN GENERAL ASSEMBLY.HE SAID THAT FROM HIS EXPERIENCE THE FOREIGN MINISTERS ARE NOT EMPOWERED TO DECIDE ANYTHING OF ANY SUBSTANCE, AND THAT EVERYTHING WOULD HAVE TO BE HANDLED IN THE CAPITALS.
NONETHELESS, HE COULD SEE WHATEVER CONVERSATIONS COULD BE TRIGGERED IN NEW YORK MIGHT SERVE A USEFUL PURPOSE.

I TOLD HIM IT WAS MY IMPRESSION THAT THE SECRETARY WOULD INDEED CONCENTRATE ON THE PROCEDURAL ROADBLOCKS TO GENEVA, BUT HE WOULD ALSO CERTAINLY BE PREPARED AND INDEED PROBABLY WISHES TO EXPLORE FURTHER THE ELMENTS OF A SUBSTANTIVE FRAMEWORK FOR NEGOTIATIONS - AS HAD OCCURED IN WASHINGTON DURING THE BEGIN VISIT.

SEEKING TO REASSURE HIM, I SAID THAT IN ANY EVENT I KNEW THE SECRETARY WOULD BE HAPPY TO "TALK SUBSTANTIVE OPTIONS" WITH DAYAN, BOTH HERE IN ISRAEL AND WHEN DAYAN CAME TO THE US AT THE TIME OF THE UNGA. 4.
DAYAN ASKED WHAT THE NEXT STEPS WOULD BE IN REGARD TO SOUTH LEBANON IN LIGHT OF THE WASHINGTON MEETINGS.
I REPLIED THAT WE PLAN TO TEST OUT THE UN PEACE- KEEPING FORCE IDEA WITH SARKIS AND PERHAPS VERY INFORMALLY WITH THE UN SECRETARY GENERAL'S STAFF;
ASSUMING ENCOURAGEMENT FROM THOSE QUARTERS, SECRETARY VANCE WOULD UNDOUBTEDLY WISH TO PURSUE IT WITH SYRIANS AND THE LEBANESE AS WELL AS THE ISRAELIS DURING HIS FORTHCOMING TRIP.
DAYAN COMMENTED FURTHER THAT A BUFFER ZONE SHOULD STRETCH AS FAR AS THE LITANI

RIVER.HE WAS CONVINCED THAT IF A UN FORCE WERE IN BEING, A REJUVENATED LEBANESE ARMY COULD BEGIN TO SUPPLY SOME STROOPS, AND IF SYRIA PLUS THE FATAH WING OF THE PLO WERE ALL BEHIND THE CONCEPT, THAT THOSE PALESTINIAN REJECTONIST UNITS NOW IN THE SOUTH COULD BE NEUTRALIZED OR PUSHED OUT SINCE THEY ARE NOT "ALL THAT NUMEROUS."
HE SAID AGAIN THAT IN HIS CONCEPT A UN PEACEKEEPING FORCE WAS REQUIRED UNTIL SUCH TIME AS THE LEBANESE ARMY IS AGAIN ABLE TO RESUME ITS REPONSIBILITIES AT THE BORDER AREA.
5.COMMENT:
DAYAN WAS CLEARLY FEELING SOMEWHAT LEFT OUT,DESPITE HAVING HAD DETAILED REPORTS FROM AMBASSADOR DINITZ ABOUT THE WASHINGTON MEETINGS.
HE IS CHAFING AT THE BIT TO GET INTO THE NEGOTIATING PROCESS HIMSELF, AS HE HAS BEEN FROM THE DAY HE ASSUMED OFFICE.
LEWIS.
UNQUOTE VANCE". ']
AGATTACHE MET WITH PERSHIN/EXPORTKHLEB TO REVIEW CURRENT IMPORT ESTIMATES REFTEL AND RECENT DEVELOPMENTS IN GRAIN PICTURE.
PERSHIN ADVISED THAT TOTAL 1975 PURCHASES INDICATED IN REFTEL WERE APPROXIMATELY CORRECT.
SPECIFIC CHANGES IN COUNTRY PURCHASES WERE NOTED.
CANADIAN PURCHASES ARE SOME- WHAT HIGHER AND WERE ATTRIBUTED TO NON-CWB PURCHASES.
US AND AUSTRALIAN DATA WERE CORRECT.
WEST EUROPEAN PURCHASES ARE ONLY 200,000 METRIC TONS -- BRAZIL, AFGENTINA AND CANADA SHARE
THE REMAINING 800,000 TONS.
PERSHIN DID NOT INDICATE ORIGIN OF EAST EUROPEAN PURCHASES, BUT ATTACHE IN PREVIOUS CONVERSATION WITH EAST EUROPEAN COUNTERPART DETERMINED THAT ROMANIA IS SOURCE OF GRAIN -- PRINCIPALLY WHEAT. 4.
OTHER FOREIGN EMBASSY SOURCES INDICATED THAT SOME CORN PURCHASED FROM BRAZIL WILL MOVE TO CUBA.
PERSHIN IMPLIED THAT SOME BULGARIAN CORN IS BEING SHIPPED TO CUBA.
HOWEVER, NO US CORN OR OTHER GRAINS WILL BE SHIPPED TO CUBA.
SOYBEAN PURCHASES OF 1.5 MILLION TONS AGAIN CONFIRMED -- ALL REPORTEDLY FOR USSR DESTINATION AND CONSUMPTION.
UNLOADING AND DISCHARGING OF GRAIN STILL ESTIMATED AT AVERAGE OF TWO MILLION TONS A MONTH WITH POSSIBILITY UP TO FOUR MILLION TONS AT PEAK CAPACITY.
INCREASED OFF-LOADINGS ABOVE AVERAGE OF TWO MILLION TONS MOST LIKELY TO OCCUR DURING SPRING AND FALL PERIODS, BUT SUCH VOLUME CANNOT BE SUSTAINED THROUGHOUT THE YEAR.
PERSHIN INDICATED THAT TEST VESSEL WITH USDA OFFICIAL ABOARD WILL ARRIVE LENINGRAD ABOUT JANUARY 5.
WOULD APPRECIATE COMMENTS ABOUT USSR GRAIN TEAM VISIT TO US.
MATLOCK ']
